This paper discusses the emergence of complex structures and dynamic properties arising from decentralized networks of interacting AI agents, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the principles of consensus in societies and finding ways to make consensus more reliable, which could fall under the categories of social and information sciences (cs.SI), multi-agent systems (cs.MA), distributed computing (cs.DC), and cybersecurity (cs.CY).
